{
  "texts": [
    "It is common for NLP benchmarks to release text from the test set, as researchers can submit a file of predictions instead of submitting code.",
    "A potential concern is that researchers can use this text during training.",
    "Consider the Real-world Annotated Fewshot Tasks (RAFT) benchmark (Alex et al., 2021), which contains \"few-shot\" text classification taskstasks where the training set contains a relatively small number of labeled examples.",
    "Below is an excerpt from the RAFT paper (emphasis added):",
    "For each task, we release a public training set with 50 examples and a larger unlabeled test set."
  ]
}